(14520, 'rank_math_seo_analysis_results', 'a:35:{s:15:"common_keywords";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:15:"common_keywords";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:15:"Common Keywords";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:81:"<p>These are the keywords that appear frequently in the text of your content.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:70:"A list of keywords that appear frequently in the text of your content.";s:7:"kb_link";s:58:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#common-keywords-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"info";s:7:"message";s:61:"Here are the most common keywords we found on your homepage: ";s:4:"data";a:10:{s:4:"home";i:3;s:7:"hustler";i:2;s:6:"tempor";i:1;s:6:"mauris";i:1;s:5:"purus";i:1;s:9:"porttitor";i:1;s:5:"learn";i:1;s:6:"recent";i:1;s:5:"posts";i:1;s:12:"moneyhustler";i:1;}}s:18:"description_length";a:12:{s:7:"test_id";s:18:"description_length";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:15:"SEO Description";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:4:"high";s:11:"description";s:400:"<p>Every HTML page should have a meta-description in the  content. Search engines read the description, so it''s a good place to introduce keywords, synonyms and supporting terminology (often referred to as "LSI keywords").</p><p>Sometimes Google will use the meta-description as the snippet that&#039;s displayed in your listing. So a well-crafted description can improve your click-through rate.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:50:"SEO analysis of your page&#039;s meta-description.";s:3:"fix";s:338:"<p>Write a meta-description for your page. Use your target keyword(s) (in a natural way) and write with human readers in mind. Summarize the content - describe the topics your article discusses.</p><p>The description should stimulate reader interest and get them to click on the article. Think of it as a mini-advert for your content.</p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:58:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#seo-description-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"fail";s:7:"message";s:48:"No meta description was found for your homepage.";s:4:"data";s:0:"";}s:10:"h1_heading";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:10:"h1_heading";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:10:"H1 Heading";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:4:"high";s:11:"description";s:1004:"<p>The HTML H1 tag plays a very important role in SEO. It&#039;s the most dominant HTML header and is usually used for article titles. H2-H4 tags are used for less important headers (usually section headers). Together, the headers on a page should build a &quot;skeleton&quot; for the content.</p><p>Each page should only have a single HTML tag. It should include the most important keywords - search engines give special weight to keywords that appear in H1 tags, as they are usually the most visible text on the page.</p><p>The H1 tag should appear near the top of the page.</p><p>Text in the H1 tag usually acts as your content&#039;s headline - readers will usually scan the headline before they read the page&#039;s full text. If your headline sparks their interest, they are more likely to stick around and read the rest of your content. If it fails to grab them, they&#039;ll probably bounce.</p><p>H1 tags are the most important text on your page - both in terms of SEO and reader engagement.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:41:"SEO Analysis of the H1 Tags on your page.";s:7:"kb_link";s:53:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#h1-heading-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:38:"One H1 tag was found on your homepage.";s:4:"data";a:1:{i:0;s:4:"Home";}}s:11:"h2_headings";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:11:"h2_headings";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:11:"H2 Headings";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:533:"<p>While the H1 heading is usually used for post titles or headlines, H2 headings are used to break your text down into logical sections.</p><p>Well chosen H2 headings help search engines to understand the structure of your content. Keywords in H2 headings carry a larger weight than text in paragraphs.</p><p>H2 headings also help to improve reader retention. Often, people scan over web pages looking for sections that catch their eye. Headings can grab their attention and get them interested in reading the rest of your text.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:45:"SEO analysis of the H2 headings on your page.";s:7:"kb_link";s:54:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#h2-headings-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:48:"One or more H2 tags were found on your homepage.";s:4:"data";a:2:{i:0;s:17:"Product Highlight";i:1;s:12:"Recent Posts";}}s:7:"img_alt";a:10:{s:7:"test_id";s:7:"img_alt";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:20:"Image ALT Attributes";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:605:"<p>Alt attributes are supposed to contain a short string of text that describes the contents of image tags. They&#039;re very useful for people who are browsing with images turned off, and they&#039;re vital for people who use screen readers.</p><p>In fact, they&#039;re a requirement for valid HTML. The W3C validator will reject a web page that uses img tags without alt attributes.</p><p>Search engines also read the contents of alt tags, to better understand the content of the page. Using your keywords (or supporting terms) in alt attributes can help to improve your content&#039;s SERP ranking.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:61:"SEO analysis of the &quot;alt&quot; attribute for image tags.";s:7:"kb_link";s:63:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#image-alt-attributes-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:48:"All images on your homepage have alt attributes.";}s:13:"keywords_meta";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:13:"keywords_meta";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:35:"Keywords in Title &amp; Description";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:1183:"<p>The title and meta description play a vital role in SEO. Keywords that appear in these places are given a higher weight by Google&#039;s ranking algorithm - because the title and description are good indicators of the subject covered by the content.</p><p>In the search results, Google will display the page title as a link (the blue underlined text). It&#039;s the most visible part of a SERP listing, and it can make or break your click-through rates.</p><p>Google will sometimes display the description in the search results (as the text snippet). People tend to read the text snippets before they decide to click on a link, so a good description can attract readers like a magnet - increasing your click-through rates.</p><p>Click through rates are very important. A higher click-through rate will naturally result in more traffic. It also sends a quality signal to Google - if a high percentage of people click on a certain link, then Google will rank that listing higher. If very few people click, then the listing could drop off the page.</p><p>In this test, we check if the most common keywords found on your page are present in the title tag and the meta description.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:72:"SEO analysis of the HTML page&#039;s Title and meta description content.";s:3:"fix";s:325:"<p>You need to use titles and descriptions that are attractive to users and contain your keywords. Use the keywords naturally - keyword stuffing is usually detected and will result in a lower ranking. What&#039;s more, it&#039;s pretty off-putting for potential readers, who are more likely to click on an appealing link.</p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:76:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#keywords-in-title-and-description-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"fail";s:7:"message";s:38:"No page description found on the page.";}s:11:"links_ratio";a:12:{s:7:"test_id";s:11:"links_ratio";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:11:"Links Ratio";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:648:"<p>External and internal links are both important for SEO.</p><p>Internal links pass PageRank around your site (PageRank is a metric that Google uses to measure the &quot;importance&quot; of web pages). They also establish topical relevance - when a page has backlinks from a page on a related topic, it helps it to rank higher for its keywords.</p><p>Google also expects to see external links in content. People like sites that link out to other high-quality resources on the web, and it&#039;s Google&#039;s goal to serve results that people like.</p><p>If your content has very few external links (or none) it can hurt its ranking potential.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:62:"SEO analysis of the ratio of internal links to external links.";s:3:"fix";s:608:"<p>Add links to external resources that are useful for your readers. Make sure you link to high-quality sites - Google penalizes pages that link to &quot;spammy&quot; sites (ones that break the Google webmaster guidelines).</p><p>Ideally, the links should be highly relevant to the subject you&#039;re writing about. It&#039;s impossible to cover every aspect of a subject on a single page, but your readers may be fascinated by some detail you barely touch on. If you link to a resource where they can learn more, they&#039;ll be grateful. What&#039;s more, you&#039;ll be rewarded with higher rankings!</p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:53:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#link-ratio-test";s:6:"status";s:7:"warning";s:7:"message";s:102:"There are one or more issues with the number of links on your homepage:<br>Too few internal links (6).";s:4:"data";a:2:{s:8:"internal";i:6;s:8:"external";i:1;}}s:12:"title_length";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:12:"title_length";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:9:"SEO Title";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:8:"priority";s:4:"high";s:11:"description";s:446:"<p>HTML page titles play a vital role in SEO. Google gives special weight to keywords that appear in the title.</p><p>Words in a page title are a very good indication of the topics covered in a page of text.</p><p>Page titles are also used as the clickable text in search result pages. Therefore, it&#039;s important to optimize your titles for humans, too.</p><p>A well-optimized title contains your main keyword(s) and gets people to click.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:44:"SEO analysis of your site&#039;s HTML title.";s:7:"kb_link";s:52:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#seo-title-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:59:"The title of your homepage has 14 characters which is good.";s:4:"data";s:14:"Home - Hustler";}s:12:"serp_preview";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:12:"serp_preview";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:14:"Search Preview";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:7:"tooltip";s:0:"";s:7:"kb_link";s:37:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/";s:6:"status";s:4:"info";s:7:"message";s:238:"Here is how your site may appear in search results:<div class="serp-preview desktop-serp-preview"><div class="serp-title">Home - Hustler</div><div class="serp-url">https://money-hustler.com/</div><div class="serp-description"></div></div>";s:4:"data";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:26:"https://money-hustler.com/";s:5:"title";s:14:"Home - Hustler";s:11:"description";s:0:"";}}s:19:"mobile_serp_preview";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:19:"mobile_serp_preview";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:21:"Mobile Search Preview";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:7:"tooltip";s:0:"";s:7:"kb_link";s:37:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/";s:6:"status";s:4:"info";s:7:"message";s:256:"Here is how your site may appear in search results on a mobile device:<div class="serp-preview mobile-serp-preview"><div class="serp-title">Home - Hustler</div><div class="serp-url">https://money-hustler.com/</div><div class="serp-description"></div></div>";s:4:"data";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:26:"https://money-hustler.com/";s:5:"title";s:14:"Home - Hustler";s:11:"description";s:0:"";}}s:15:"mobile_snapshot";a:12:{s:7:"test_id";s:15:"mobile_snapshot";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:15:"Mobile Snapshot";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:790:"<p>Here&#039;s a snapshot of how your site looks on a mobile device - we&#039;ve used the most common dimensions.</p><p>Sites that look good on desktop computers can look terrible on mobile devices. They can also suffer from usability issues.</p><p>Google&#039;s algorithm uses a very advanced set of tests to analyze how your site performs on mobile devices. It has a comprehensive checklist of usability issues to check for, such as link size (smaller links are harder to click accurately on a tiny screen).</p><p>Google gives a ranking boost to sites that support mobile devices (especially for searches from a phone or tablet).</p><p>Improving your site&#039;s appearance and usability on mobile devices will also improve your user engagement, which should result in higher revenue.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:58:"A snapshot of how your content appears on a mobile device.";s:3:"fix";s:319:"<p>Use a theme or template with great mobile support. If you&#039;re using a custom theme, use Google&#039;s free PageSpeed Insights tools to test the mobile performance and usability issues. Fix every point that PageSpeed reports - these are all factors that can hurt your site&#039;s rankings for mobile searches.</p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:37:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/";s:6:"status";s:4:"info";s:7:"message";s:114:"<img src="https://image.thum.io/get/auth/3406-rmthumb/iphone6/https://money-hustler.com/" style="max-width:100%;">";s:4:"data";s:78:"https://image.thum.io/get/auth/3406-rmthumb/iphone6/https://money-hustler.com/";}s:9:"canonical";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:9:"canonical";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:13:"Canonical Tag";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:4:"high";s:11:"description";s:2196:"<p>Under the original vision of the web, every HTML document was unique and had a single URL. As the web grew, we quickly learned that that presumption is false.</p><p>Often, a web page can be accessed using many URLs. In other words, a web server will serve the same content for different URLs. For instance, WordPress uses a permalink structure with variables in the URL, like this: http://somesite.com/?p=10</p><p>These variables tell WordPress which page or post you want to read. Of course, it&#039;s not very pretty or SEO friendly, so WordPress allows you to change the permalink structure to virtually anything you prefer.</p><p>Behind the scenes, WordPress uses Apache&#039;s URL Rewriting Module to translate the pretty URLs into the basic ones, complete with the variables. That means that WordPress will recognize the pretty URLs OR the ugly ones.</p><p>In other words, you can access the same content with 2 (or more) URLs.</p><p>The result is &quot;duplicate content&quot; - that&#039;s an issue in SEO terms. When Google finds the exact same content at 2 different URLs, it doesn&#039;t know which version is the &quot;right&quot; one. Which version should it index and list in the search results?</p><p>Ambiguous URLs are not the only way that duplicate content pops up. Content syndication is another source of trouble. When people republish articles from other sites (with the author&#039;s permission), Google often has a hard time understanding which is the original article.</p><p>It doesn&#039;t want to serve the same content over and over, so it will filter out some of the results. But it can make a mistake and filter out the original.</p><p>What&#039;s more, if Google finds too much duplicate content on a site, it could decide the site doesn&#039;t have enough unique content to index or justify the cost of crawling it. This can make it extremely hard to get your site fully indexed, and can drastically limit your ability to rank and drive search traffic.</p><p>&quot;Canonicalization&quot; means telling the search engines which URL is the &quot;right&quot; (or &quot;canonical&quot;) one. It prevents your content from falling into the duplicate content trap.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:51:"Does your content have a &quot;canonical&quot; URL?";s:7:"kb_link";s:56:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#canonical-tag-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:46:"Your homepage is using the canonical link tag.";s:4:"data";s:26:"https://money-hustler.com/";}s:7:"noindex";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:7:"noindex";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:12:"Noindex Meta";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:492:"<p>Robots meta tags are designed to control what a search engine spider does with your content. You may want to keep some pages out of the search engines - that&#039;s why Google proposed a &quot;noindex&quot; option.</p><p>If your page has a &quot;noindex&quot; robots meta tag, Google won&#039;t index it. It won&#039;t appear in search results, and it won&#039;t drive any search traffic.</p><p>In most cases, this is the absolute opposite of what you&#039;re trying to achieve in SEO.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:52:"Does your content contain a noindex robots meta tag?";s:7:"kb_link";s:55:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#noindex-meta-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:65:"Your homepage contains the <code>index</code> meta tag or header.";s:4:"data";a:2:{s:6:"header";a:0:{}s:4:"meta";a:0:{}}}s:7:"non_www";a:10:{s:7:"test_id";s:7:"non_www";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:20:"WWW Canonicalization";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:800:"<p>Some sites show the same content for different URLs. For instance, if you visit http://www.example.com, you see the same content as http://example.com. </p><p>That can cause problems for SEO - search engines see duplicate content, which they hate.</p><p>Duplicate content can muddy your rankings, as Google isn&#039;t sure which page to rank. It can hurt your backlink count and PageRank, too. Some people will link to the &quot;www&quot; version, others will omit it. With the backlinks split between two &quot;different&quot; pages, your content will get a lower search rank than it deserves.</p><p>WWW Canonicalization means picking a URL and sticking to it. It doesn&#039;t matter if you choose the www. version or prefer the plain domain name (http://example.com) - at least in SEO terms.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:43:"Does your site appear on more than one URL?";s:7:"kb_link";s:63:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#www-canonicalization-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:74:"Both www and non-www versions of your URL are redirected to the same site.";}s:9:"opengraph";a:12:{s:7:"test_id";s:9:"opengraph";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:14:"OpenGraph Meta";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:687:"<p>OpenGraph is a meta tag standard used by social websites. It allows you to control how your link is displayed on a social site - including the image, the title, a description, and possibly an extra link to your author profile.</p><p>With OpenGraph meta tags, you can tweak your content to capture more attention on social channels and get more traffic.</p><p>It can also trigger more &quot;social signals&quot;, which most SEO experts agree play a strong role in Google&#039;s ranking algorithm.</p><p>Facebook invented the OpenGraph standard, but other sites have been quick to adopt it. So implementing OpenGraph markup should lead to an increased response on multiple channels.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:39:"Does your site use OpenGraph meta tags?";s:3:"fix";s:404:"<p>Insert a customized OpenGraph meta tag for each important page on your site. The standard is very well documented - you can learn more from Facebook&#039;s developer pages.</p><p>The Rank Math WordPress plugin provides a simple but powerful interface to craft your OpenGraph data. You get immediate feedback with an interactive preview, and you don&#039;t have to mess around with raw HTML markup.</p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:58:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#open-graph-meta-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"fail";s:7:"message";s:37:"Some Opengraph meta tags are missing.";s:4:"data";a:2:{s:4:"tags";a:5:{s:6:"locale";s:5:"en_US";s:4:"type";s:7:"website";s:5:"title";s:14:"Home - Hustler";s:3:"url";s:26:"https://money-hustler.com/";s:12:"updated_time";s:25:"2023-08-14T12:10:58+00:00";}s:7:"missing";a:2:{i:0;s:11:"description";i:1;s:5:"image";}}}s:10:"robots_txt";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:10:"robots_txt";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:10:"Robots.txt";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:615:"<p>Robots.txt files are used to control bots and spiders - automated programs that visit your site.</p><p>Control is a bit of a strong word in this context. A robots.txt file is just a plain-text file that lives in your web root. It has no actual power to stop bots from requesting resources from your site.</p><p>Nevertheless, it&#039;s a recognized standard, and the most reputable bots (such as Google&#039;s bot) will respect the directives.</p><p>You can use a robots.txt file to prevent bots from accessing certain parts of your site - so you can select which content you want the search engines to index.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:43:"Does your site have a valid robots.txt file";s:7:"kb_link";s:53:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#robots-txt-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:159:"Your site has a robots.txt file which includes one or more <code>Disallow:</code> directives. Make sure that you only block parts you don''t want to be indexed.";s:4:"data";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}}s:6:"schema";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:6:"schema";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:16:"Schema Meta Data";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:622:"<p>Schema.org is a standards-friendly extension of HTML that allows you to add meaning to your markup. It&#039;s a step towards the &quot;semantic web&quot;, where systems can extract meaning from web pages (instead of mere text strings).</p><p>That sounds cool, but does it have any real-world applications? Actually, it does.</p><p>Google recognizes many Schema.org tags and uses them to better understand your content. This can result in extremely eye-grabbing &quot;rich snippets.&quot; Basically, that means your listing can stand out from other results on the page, resulting in a much higher click-through rate.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:55:"Does your content include relevant Schema.org metadata?";s:7:"kb_link";s:59:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#schema-meta-data-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:48:"Schema.org data has been found on your homepage.";s:4:"data";a:2:{s:6:"schema";b:1;s:7:"json_ld";b:1;}}s:12:"image_header";a:10:{s:7:"test_id";s:12:"image_header";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:20:"Image Headers Expire";s:8:"category";s:11:"performance";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:780:"<p>The &quot;Expires&quot; HTTP header is a line from the response the web server sends to a client. It tells the browser how long it should cache a file for. Ideally, you should use long durations for files that are unlikely to change - these are usually called &quot;static files&quot;.</p><p>Images are a prime example of static files. In 99.99% of all cases, the images on published web pages are not going to change. And if you do edit an image from a published page, you can change the file name.</p><p>So in most cases, you should always use an &quot;expires&quot; header for images.</p><p>Sometimes sites use scripts to generate images - such as graphs. If these generated images change very frequently (second by second), you wouldn&#039;t use caching for that image.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:47:"Do your images use &quot;expires&quot; headers?";s:7:"kb_link";s:63:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#image-headers-expire-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:34:"No local images found on the page.";}s:10:"minify_css";a:12:{s:7:"test_id";s:10:"minify_css";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:10:"Minify CSS";s:8:"category";s:11:"performance";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:483:"<p>Reducing the size of your site&#039;s files will make them download faster. Compression makes files smaller, but that&#039;s not the only method.</p><p>Minification is a process to remove unnecessary characters from code files - like CSS, JavaScript, XML, and HTML.</p><p>CSS files often have comments, white space (tabs and spaces) and other unnecessary characters. Web browsers can understand CSS perfectly without them, so there&#039;s no reason to send them over the wire.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:37:"Are your CSS files properly minified?";s:3:"fix";s:264:"<p>CSS can add a lot of load-time to your website. Thankfully, there is an easy solution to minify CSS using the popular W3 Total Cache plugin. <a href="https://mythemeshop.com/blog/w3-total-cache-tutorial/#general-section-minify" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:53:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#minify-css-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"fail";s:7:"message";s:46:"Some CSS files don&#039;t seem to be minified.";s:4:"data";a:1:{i:0;s:272:"https://money-hustler.com/_jb_static/??-eJydj8sOgkAMRf/GlUMlBqIL4reUocGReWVaQubvHdQFJC6Mu970nKYXlqiM13YeiEEzw2BYoLdBT8qaPmHKwJItVc74qgBH2BoPBkeDQbLkyMsuRIuZkrI0os6/6WW3zTtJBy8rI/eyYxjJU0KhmKh8jcwk7wI6uBh8IRkWM4wkChMh/3XLYZG+idHOo/GlAElEPb3gz7yyN9fV7bW5nNu2OR1039VPhEuGvg==";}}s:9:"minify_js";a:12:{s:7:"test_id";s:9:"minify_js";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:17:"Minify Javascript";s:8:"category";s:11:"performance";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:954:"<p>Big files take longer to download than small ones. And some text files are bloated - they contain characters that aren&#039;t necessary for the code to work.</p><p>JavaScript files are usually written for human readability - which makes sense. Developers usually spend hours editing and writing them, so they have to be easy to read.</p><p>Web browsers care nothing about readability. They simply parse, compile and run the JavaScript.</p><p>Minification is the process that reduces the size of a Javascript file. It replaces all the variable and function names with very short names, and strips out all the whitespace.</p><p>The result is a much smaller file that&#039;s almost impossible for a human to read and understand. It will download much faster, but it&#039;s a nightmare to debug.</p><p>That&#039;s why minification is usually the last step of development - don&#039;t minify your javascript until you&#039;re ready to launch your site.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:39:"Does your site use minified JavaScript?";s:3:"fix";s:531:"<p>JavaScript files appear in many places, including frameworks (like Bootstrap), themes and templates, and third-party plugins.</p><p>So you should track down where the culprit (un-minified) JavaScript files come from. For instance, if the un-minified JavaScript lives inside a third party plugin, you can minify it. But when you update the plugin to a new version, the JavaScript files will need to be compressed again.</p><p>There are server-side tools (including WordPress plugins) to automatically minify JavaScript files.</p>";s:7:"kb_link";s:61:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#minify-java-script-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"fail";s:7:"message";s:53:"Some Javascript files don&#039;t seem to be minified.";s:4:"data";a:1:{i:0;s:316:"https://money-hustler.com/_jb_static/??-eJy1kE1uAjEMhW/TFcFCFSNYoF6gd6hCxgwZxk4UOyA4PWb4EaqQqqrqyrGt9/nlwSG7kFiRFfJQu8gCXXa5IMVKQMjV2VxgUzloTLbuBURj2B2nFHnaywReMHrU7MPuXr/2yG0q4Ksm8mry+8ZF8h260DK0URQe7XeybpHQzCFj8YrmUAS8COpoKQz2/jTCK1c/aC+//K1sNEup9cPfIxj86XjN4caNRiqCY+AurQXLHss/3HkaGP2DVrNmOV+8N02zeAvr1ewMJRHNrw==";}}s:12:"page_objects";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:12:"page_objects";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:12:"Page Objects";s:8:"category";s:11:"performance";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:736:"<p>Objects are files that are embedded into a web page. This usually includes content like video, rich media, Java Applets, PDF, Flash and other binary files.</p><p>These objects can add great functionality to a site, but that usually comes at a performance cost. For instance, an embedded Java Applet requires a separate process to handle - the browser cannot support it natively. The browser needs to launch a plugin to run the content in object tags.</p><p>HTML 5 has provided some alternatives for page objects. You can often replace Java Applets with native JavaScript and canvas tags, for instance.</p><p>A page with a lot of embedded objects will have worse performance, and that can hurt your rankings in the search engines.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:47:"Analysis of the embedded objects in your pages.";s:7:"kb_link";s:55:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#page-objects-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:31:"Your homepage makes 7 requests.";s:4:"data";a:4:{s:5:"total";i:7;s:6:"images";i:0;s:10:"javascript";i:5;s:11:"stylesheets";i:2;}}s:9:"page_size";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:9:"page_size";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:9:"Page Size";s:8:"category";s:11:"performance";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:325:"<p>Larger HTML files take longer to download. And the browser needs to download the entire file before it can render your content.</p><p>So it&#039;s a good idea to reduce the size of your HTML files.</p><p>Google&#039;s ranking algorithm favors sites with good performance, and HTML size is one of the factors it weighs.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:42:"An analysis of the size of your HTML file.";s:7:"kb_link";s:52:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#page-size-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:77:"The size of the HTML document is 14 Kb, under the average HTML size of 33 Kb.";s:4:"data";i:14548;}s:13:"response_time";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:13:"response_time";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:13:"Response Time";s:8:"category";s:11:"performance";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:797:"<p>Performance is a hot issue - it affects user engagement and your rankings. Performance optimization begins with server response time.</p><p>Server response time is basically how long it takes for the server to send a requested file. It&#039;s the time between the client request and the first bytes arriving down the wire.</p><p>If you use a CMS like WordPress, the job of serving a request can be quite complex. The server doesn&#039;t just load a file from the hard disk and send it to the user. Instead, it has to build an HTML page from a variety of sources. Your content is stored in a database. The theme is stored in several files. Plugins add their content to the mix. And all this data has to be processed to render the HTML.</p><p>This can increase the response time considerably.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:46:"How fast does your server respond to requests?";s:7:"kb_link";s:56:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#response-time-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:55:"Your response time is under 0.2 seconds which is great.";s:4:"data";d:0.162015999999999993352872706964262761175632476806640625;}s:14:"active_plugins";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:14:"active_plugins";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:15:"Visible Plugins";s:8:"category";s:8:"security";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:26:"<p>Test description...</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:15:"Visible Plugins";s:7:"kb_link";s:53:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#visible-plugins";s:6:"status";s:4:"info";s:7:"message";s:50:"Hurray! None of your plugins are publicly visible.";s:4:"data";a:0:{}}s:12:"active_theme";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:12:"active_theme";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:16:"Theme Visibility";s:8:"category";s:8:"security";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:26:"<p>Test description...</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:16:"Theme Visibility";s:7:"kb_link";s:59:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#theme-visibility-test";s:6:"status";s:4:"info";s:7:"message";s:86:"Hurray! Your theme is not publicly visible. No one can tell which theme you are using.";s:4:"data";b:0;}s:17:"directory_listing";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:17:"directory_listing";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:17:"Directory Listing";s:8:"category";s:8:"security";s:8:"priority";s:6:"medium";s:11:"description";s:411:"<p>Many web server programs are designed to simply list the contents of a directory when there&#039;s no &quot;index.html&quot; file. It&#039;s a standard behavior - in fact, that&#039;s how the first web servers behaved.</p><p>Unfortunately, it&#039;s also a huge security hole. Allowing a potential hacker to read the contents of your web directories makes it easier for them to find potential weaknesses.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:58:"Does your web server list the contents of the directories?";s:7:"kb_link";s:60:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#directory-listing-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:54:"Directory Listing seems to be disabled on your server.";s:4:"data";s:0:"";}s:3:"ssl";a:10:{s:7:"test_id";s:3:"ssl";s:8:"api_test";b:1;s:5:"title";s:17:"Secure Connection";s:8:"category";s:8:"security";s:8:"priority";s:4:"high";s:11:"description";s:667:"<p>HTTPS is a secure version of the HTTP protocol - it uses a secure connection to ensure nobody can intercept the communication between your user and your server.</p><p>With many sites collecting private information from users, HTTPs has become an important part of today&#039;s web. Google has played a large role in the &quot;HTTPS only&quot; movement, recommending that every site switch to HTTPS and educating web developers on the best practices.</p><p>Google has also confirmed that HTTPS is a ranking factor - sites that use HTTPS rank higher than sites that don&#039;t.</p><p>If you haven&#039;t switched to HTTPS yet, you should make it a high priority.</p>";s:7:"tooltip";s:48:"Is your content served over a secure connection?";s:7:"kb_link";s:60:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/#secure-connection-test";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:54:"Your site is using a secure transfer protocol (https).";}s:11:"auto_update";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:11:"auto_update";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:17:"Automatic Updates";s:11:"description";s:88:"Enable automatic updates to ensure you are always using the latest version of Rank Math.";s:3:"fix";s:0:"";s:8:"category";s:8:"priority";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:47:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#priority";s:7:"tooltip";s:45:"Verify auto-updates are enabled for Rank Math";s:6:"status";s:7:"warning";s:7:"message";s:284:"<div class="auto-update-disabled">Automatic updates are not enabled on your site. <a href="#" class="button button-primary button-small enable-auto-update">Enable Auto Updates</a></div><div class="auto-update-enabled hidden">Rank Math auto-update option is enabled on your site.</div>";}s:16:"site_description";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:16:"site_description";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:12:"Site Tagline";s:11:"description";s:275:"Your theme may display the Site Tagline, and it can also be used in SEO titles &amp; descriptions. Set it to something unique. You can change it by navigating to &lt;a href=&quot;https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/options-general.php&quot;&gt;Settings &gt; General&lt;/a&gt;.";s:3:"fix";s:909:"<p>Most WordPress themes place your site&#039;s tagline in a prominent position (inside header tags near the top of the page).  Using the right tagline can give your site an SEO boost.</p><p>Unfortunately, the standard WordPress tagline is &quot;Just Another WordPress site.&quot;  That&#039;s pretty sloppy looking, and it does nothing for your SEO.  In fact, it&#039;s actually a security risk - it makes it easy for hackers with a WordPress exploit to locate your site with an automated search.</p><p>Changing your tagline is very easy.  Just head on over to <a target="_blank" href="https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/options-general.php">Settings - General</a> in WordPress''s admin menu (on the left), or click on the link in this sentence.</p><p>The tagline is the second option.  Choose a tagline that summarizes your site in a few words.  The tagline is also a good place to use your main keyword.</p>";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:56:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#site-tagline-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:43:"Confirm custom tagline is set for your site";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:43:"Your Site Tagline is set to a custom value.";}s:11:"blog_public";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:11:"blog_public";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:11:"Blog Public";s:11:"description";s:46:"Your site may not be visible to search engine.";s:3:"fix";s:162:"<p>You must <a href="https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/options-reading.php">go to your Reading Settings</a> and uncheck the box for Search Engine Visibility.</p>";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:55:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#blog-public-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:51:"Check your site&#039;s visibility to search engines";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:41:"Your site is accessible by search engine.";}s:19:"permalink_structure";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:19:"permalink_structure";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:19:"Permalink Structure";s:11:"description";s:261:"For the best SEO results, use a custom permalink structure, preferably one that includes the post title (<code>%postname%</code>). You can change it by navigating to <a href="https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/options-permalink.php">Settings &gt; Permalinks</a>";s:3:"fix";s:809:"<p>The standard permalink structure is pretty ugly - WordPress generates offputting URLs like: http://www.yoursite.com/?p=99</p><p>It&#039;s not very kind on the eyes, and it does nothing for your site&#039;s SEO.  In fact, it can hurt it - Google&#039;s bot is quite cautious about crawling pages that look auto-generated.</p><p>Fortunately, it''s very easy to fix.  Just hop on over to <a target="_blank" href="https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/options-permalink.php">Settings - Permalinks</a>.  Then chose the "Post Name" option.</p><p>This option will replace the &quot;?p=99&quot; part of the URL with the post&#039;s title, like this: http://www.yoursite.com/my-amazing-post-title/</p><p>This looks nice for readers - and it gets your keywords into the URL (keywords in the URL is a ranking factor).</p>";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:63:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#permalink-structure-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:52:"Check your site for SEO-friendly permalink structure";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:85:"Post permalink structure is set to <code>/%year%/%monthnum%/%day%/%postname%/</code>.";}s:14:"focus_keywords";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:14:"focus_keywords";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:14:"Focus Keywords";s:11:"description";s:78:"Setting focus keywords for your posts allows Rank Math to analyse the content.";s:3:"fix";s:652:"<p>Rank Math allows you to set a focus keyword for every post and page you write - the option is in the &quot;Meta Box&quot;, which appears under the text editor in the screen where you write and edit content.</p><p>Rank Math uses these focus keywords to analyze your on-page content.  It can tell if you&#039;ve done a good job of optimizing your text to rank for these keywords.</p><p>Of course, if you don&#039;t give Rank Math a focus keyword to work with, it can&#039;t give you any useful feedback.</p><p>Fixing this issue is easy - just edit the post, and set a Focus Keyword.  Then follow Rank Math&#039;s analysis to improve your rankings.</p>";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:58:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#focus-keywords-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:49:"Confirm focus keywords are set for all your posts";s:6:"status";s:4:"fail";s:7:"message";s:149:"There are <a href="https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/edit.php?post_type=page&focus_keyword=1" target="_blank">7 Pages</a> with no focus keyword set.";}s:11:"post_titles";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:11:"post_titles";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:34:"Post Titles Missing Focus Keywords";s:11:"description";s:74:"Make sure the focus keywords you set for the posts appear in their titles.";s:3:"fix";s:394:"<p>HTML Page Titles play a large role in Google&#039;s ranking algorithm.  When you add a Focus Keyword to a post or page, Rank Math will check to see that you used the keyword in the title.  If it finds any posts or pages that are missing the keyword in the title, it will tell you here.</p><p>Fixing the issue is simple - just edit the post/page and add the focus keyword(s) to the title.</p>";s:8:"category";s:5:"basic";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:78:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#post-titles-missing-focus-keywords-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:57:"Verify the presence of focus keywords in your post titles";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:71:"Focus keywords appear in the titles of published posts where it is set.";}s:14:"search_console";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:14:"search_console";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:14:"Search Console";s:11:"description";s:466:"Register at Google Search Console and verificate your site by adding the code to &lt;a href=&quot;https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/admin.php?page=rank-math-options-general#setting-panel-webmaster&quot;&gt;Settings &gt; Verificate Tools&lt;/a&gt;, then navigate to &lt;a href=&quot;https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/admin.php?page=rank-math-options-general#setting-panel-analytics&quot;&gt;Settings &gt; Search Console&lt;/a&gt; to authenticate and link your site.";s:3:"fix";s:786:"<p>Google&#039;s Search Console is a vital source of information concerning your rankings and click-through rates.  Rank Math can import this data, so you don&#039;t have to log into your Google account to get the data you need.</p><p>You can integrate the Google Search Console with Rank math in the <a href="https://money-hustler.com/wp-admin/admin.php?page=rank-math-options-general#setting-panel-analytics" target="_blank">Search Console tab</a>. of Rank Math''s General Settings menu.</p><p>Read <a href="https://rankmath.com/kb/analytics/?utm_source=Plugin&utm_medium=SEO%20Analysis%20GSC%20Test&utm_campaign=WP" target="_blank">this article</a> for detailed instructions on setting up your Google Webmaster account and getting Rank Math to work with the Google Search Console.</p>";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:58:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#search-console-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:51:"Confirm if Rank Math is connected to Search Console";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:38:"Google Search Console has been linked.";}s:8:"sitemaps";a:11:{s:7:"test_id";s:8:"sitemaps";s:8:"api_test";b:0;s:5:"title";s:8:"Sitemaps";s:11:"description";s:551:"XML sitemaps are a special type of text file that tells search engines about the structure of your site. They&#039;re a list of all the resources (pages and files) you would like the search engine to index. You can assign different priorities, so certain pages will be crawled first. Before XML sitemaps, search engines were limited to indexing the content they could find by following links. That&#039;s still an important feature for search engine spiders, but XML sitemaps have made it easier for content creators and search engines to collaborate.";s:3:"fix";s:527:"If you don&#039;t have an XML sitemap, the best option is to install a plugin that creates sitemaps for you. That way you&#039;ll know the sitemap will always be up-to-date. Plugins can also automatically ping the search engines when the XML file is updated. The Rank Math WordPress plugin gives you complete control over your site&#039;s XML sitemaps. You can control the settings for each page as you write or edit it, and Rank Math will ping Google as soon as you submit your edits. This results in fast crawls and indexing.";s:8:"category";s:8:"advanced";s:4:"info";a:0:{}s:7:"kb_link";s:52:"https://rankmath.com/kb/seo-analysis/?#sitemaps-test";s:7:"tooltip";s:46:"Check the presence of sitemaps on your website";s:6:"status";s:2:"ok";s:7:"message";s:35:"Your site has one or more sitemaps.";}}', 'no');
